The paper discusses a theoretical framework and algorithm for improving the efficiency of mutation-based fuzzing, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also focuses on finding security-relevant bugs, which suggests a potential fit for the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions targeting open-source programs and file formats, which could relate to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm and compares it to existing methods, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG).
